# Text Area

A multi-line text input that auto-grows with longer content.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/field
import ui/text_area

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  field.root([field.vertical(), attribute.class("w-96")], [
    field.label([attribute.for("intro-description")], [
      html.text("Description"),
    ]),
    text_area.input(
      [
        attribute.id("intro-description"),
        attribute.placeholder("Tell us what changed in this release…"),
      ],
      "",
    ),
  ])
}
```

## Installation

Install this element and its dependencies with the Drip CLI:

```sh
gleam run -m drip -- add text_area
```

## Usage

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/field
import ui/text_area

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  field.root([field.vertical()], [
    field.label([attribute.for("description")], [html.text("Description")]),
    text_area.input(
      [attribute.id("description"), attribute.placeholder("Add a description…")],
      "",
    ),
  ])
}
```

## Examples

Set the state of a text area with standard attributes, or compose it with field helpers.

### Default

A bare text area inside a field, with placeholder copy. Auto-sizes to its content via field-sizing.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/field
import ui/text_area

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  field.root([field.vertical(), attribute.class("w-96")], [
    field.label([attribute.for("release-notes")], [html.text("Release Notes")]),
    text_area.input(
      [
        attribute.id("release-notes"),
        attribute.placeholder("v0.2.0: what shipped?"),
      ],
      "",
    ),
  ])
}
```

### Required

Pass the required attribute and the field's label surfaces an accent asterisk.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/field
import ui/text_area

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  field.root([field.vertical(), attribute.class("w-96")], [
    field.label([attribute.for("rollback-reason")], [
      html.text("Rollback Reason"),
    ]),
    text_area.input(
      [
        attribute.id("rollback-reason"),
        attribute.placeholder("What went wrong?"),
        attribute.required(True),
      ],
      "",
    ),
    field.description([], [html.text("Posted to the incident channel.")]),
  ])
}
```

### Invalid

Set aria-invalid to surface the destructive border. Pair with field.error for the message.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/field
import ui/text_area

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  field.root([field.vertical(), attribute.class("w-96")], [
    field.label([attribute.for("commit-message")], [
      html.text("Commit Message"),
    ]),
    text_area.input(
      [
        attribute.id("commit-message"),
        attribute.aria_invalid("true"),
        attribute.placeholder("Describe your change…"),
      ],
      "wip",
    ),
    field.error([], [
      html.text("Commit messages must be at least 10 characters."),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

### Disabled

Add the disabled attribute to lock a text area and dim its surface.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/field
import ui/text_area

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  field.root([field.vertical(), attribute.class("w-96")], [
    field.label([attribute.for("generated-summary")], [
      html.text("Generated Summary"),
    ]),
    text_area.input(
      [
        attribute.id("generated-summary"),
        attribute.placeholder("No summary generated yet…"),
        attribute.disabled(True),
      ],
      "Auto-generated by the deploy pipeline. Edit the source PR to change.",
    ),
    field.description([], [html.text("Edit the source PR to regenerate.")]),
  ])
}
```

## API Reference

### Elements

A single element that renders a native textarea. Text comes from the content argument.

| Element | Description |
| --- | --- |
| `text_area.input(attrs, content)` | Multi-line text input that auto-grows with its content. |

### Attributes

Standard Lustre attributes and events the text area responds to. Pass them through the attribute list.

| Attribute | Description |
| --- | --- |
| `attribute.placeholder(...)` | Hint text shown when the text area is empty. |
| `event.on_input(...)` | Message dispatched on every keystroke with the current value. |
| `attribute.aria_invalid("true")` | Surfaces the validation state: destructive border and error ring. |
| `attribute.required(True)` | Marks the text area as required; field.label surfaces an indicator. |
| `attribute.disabled(True)` | Locks the text area, blocks pointer events, and reduces opacity. |
| `attribute.rows(...)` | Fallback height for browsers without field-sizing support. |

### Selectors

CSS selectors stamped on the text area's markup, available for overriding or layering app-specific styles.

| Selector | Matches |
| --- | --- |
| `[data-slot="text-area"]` | The text area control. |
| `[data-slot="text-area"]:focus-visible` | A focused text area, showing its focus outline. |
| `[data-slot="text-area"][aria-invalid="true"]` | A text area in its validation-failure state. |
| `[data-slot="text-area"]:disabled` | A locked, non-interactive text area. |

## Accessibility

**Native semantics, validation aware.** Renders as a native `<textarea>` with full keyboard support, surfaces validation via aria-invalid, and uses field-sizing so the control grows with its content rather than masking overflow. Pair each control with a label element for screen readers.

### Keyboard

| Key | Action |
| --- | --- |
| Tab | Move focus to the next focusable control. |
| Shift + Tab | Move focus to the previous focusable control. |
| Enter | Insert a newline at the caret. |

